{"title":"How to watch the Vuelta Femenina 2024","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-vuelta-femenina","date":1714149586000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-vuelta-femenina\">How to watch the Vuelta Femenina 2024</a></p>\n\n<p>The women’s Grand Tour cycle commences at the 2024 Vuelta Femenina. The race will offer the first top-tier stage race showdown this year for the women, with a difficult week of racing in Spain on the agenda.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/la-vuelta-femenina-preview\" target=\"_blank\">The route has been expanded to eight stages in 2024</a>. The race will begin in Valencia with a team time-trial on Sunday 28th April and will conclude with a mountain stage to Valdesquí on Sunday 5th May. The race will feature three mountain stages, some signature punchy Vuelta finishes and a healthy sprinkling of sprints.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The race boasts <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/vuelta-femenina-favourites\" target=\"_blank\">a startlist including GC contenders</a> Demi Vollering, Elisa Longo Borghini, Kasia Niewiadoma among others. The sprinters include Charlotte Kool and Marianne Vos, and expect a whole host of names to emerge among the greats at the women’s Vuelta.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/vuelta-femenina-favourites\">Who are the favourites for the Vuelta Femenina 2024?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/opinion-mens-cycling-2024\">Opinion: Men’s cycling has never been more bleak for fans</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/la-vuelta-femenina-preview\">La Vuelta Femenina 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2024: Stage-by-stage preview and how to watch</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>How to watch the Vuelta Femenina 2024</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GJL_x_nXYAE44MO-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Vuelta Femenina 2024 will be available to watch in the UK on Eurosport and <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> for £6.99 per month with the basic package, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. Stages 1 to 6 will also be shown live in the UK on the TV channel Eurosport 2. Highlights packages of Stages 7 and 8 will be shown on Eurosport 1 after the opening stages of the men’s Giro d’Italia.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find a way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs £5.36 per month, with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling post-GCN</a></strong> </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>La Vuelta Femenina 2024 TV and streaming times</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling-350x233.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/FvhWJp_WwAMjEGu-SprintCycling.jpeg 2000w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./SprintCycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All times BST and subject to change by broadcasters </em></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Valencia – Valencia, 16km (TTT)</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Sunday 28th April</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:30 – 16:15<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 15:00 – 16:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Buñol/Bunyol – Moncofa, 118.5k</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Monday 29th April</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 14:30 – 16:15<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 14:30 – 16:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Lucena/Llucena – Teruel, 130.5km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Tuesday 30th April</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 14:30 – 16:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 14:30 – 16:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Molina de Aragón – Zaragoza, 142.5km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Wednesday 1st May</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 14:30 – 16:15<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 14:30 – 16:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Huesca – Jaca, 114km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Thursday 2nd May</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 14:30 – 16:15<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 14:30 – 16:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6: Tarazona – La Laguna Negra (Vinuesa), 132.5km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Friday 3rd May</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 13:30 – 15:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 13:30 – 15:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 7: San Esteban de Gormaz – Sigüenza, 139km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Saturday 4th May</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 13:00 – 15:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 16:45 – 17:45*</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 8: Distrito Telefónica – Valdesquí, 89.5km</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Sunday 5th May</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 11:00 – 13:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 16:45 – 17:45*</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>* Highlights to be shown directly after coverage of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\" target=\"_blank\">men’s Giro d’Italia</a> on Eurosport 1</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Full list of broadcasters</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-2048x1365.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/e90cc-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption>Rafa Gomez/SprintCycling</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Australia:</strong> SBS<br /><strong>Belgium:</strong> RTBF<br /><strong>Canada: </strong>FloBikes<br /><strong>Colombia:</strong> RTVC Señal<br /><strong>Denmark: </strong>TV2<br /><strong>Europe:</strong> Discovery+, Eurosport<br /><strong>Japan:</strong> JSports<br /><strong>Latin America and Caribbean: </strong>ESPN<br /><strong>Middle East and North Africa: </strong>SSC<br /><strong>Netherlands: </strong>NOS<br /><strong>Norway: </strong>TV2<br /><strong>New Zealand: </strong>Sky Sport<br /><strong>South East Asia &amp; Pacific:</strong> Eurosport Asia<br /><strong>Spain:</strong> RTVE<br /><strong>Subsaharan Africa:</strong> Supersport<br /><strong>United States:</strong> Peacock</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Want to know more about the Vuelta Femenina 2024? <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/la-vuelta-femenina-preview\" target=\"_blank\">Read our full preview available here.</a></em></p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/vuelta-